trend_summary: Central township enlarged slightly while most growth occurred in scattered edge hamlets and a new industrial park in the northwest. Farmland plots consolidated, with some eastern tracts reverting to forest and several western fields irrigated. Overall green cover rises modestly; built-up footprint remains limited versus vast agricultural land.
notable_changes: Incremental housing infill and edge expansion around the main central settlement.
Construction of a large light-roofed industrial/warehouse complex in the northwest quadrant.
Field boundaries merged, producing larger rectangular crop blocks across the south-central corridor.
Eastern river corridor gains forest cover where marginal cropland is abandoned.
New irrigation ponds and greener irrigated patches appear in western farms.
